                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "PURPOSE"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 10,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "The purpose of this Standard Operating Procedure (SOP) is to:"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 11,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for recording referrals for diagnostic requests from GPs."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 12,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Document and standardise the process for tracking and updating the patient's pathway status to ensure accurate RTT information is recorded"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 13,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Provide a baseline for future process improvements"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 14,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Assist in developing baseline for the development of training material"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 15,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Overview"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 16,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "MEHT receive diagnostic requests for patients from GPs; these patients are not subject to 18 week RTT monitoring. A new referral must be added in Lorenzo to record and book these requests; however an 18 week RTT pathway must not be started for these referrals in Lorenzo as they must be recorded as non RTT monitored activities in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 17,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "The information recorded when adding these referrals in Lorenzo must be selected with attention to ensure that RTT is not triggered."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 18,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Additional guidance"
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 19,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 0,
                "text": "Prior to adding a new referral to a patient's record, the user must review the active referrals in the referrals tab of patients EPR in Lorenzo, to see if the patient has an active referral in the same service for the same request. If this is the case then a new referral must not be created as this will start a new pathway in Lorenzo."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 20,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Staff must escalate referrals that have incomplete details to their supervisor before this can be added to Lorenzo EPR."
            }
        },
        {
            "type": "ListItem",
            "sequence_num": 21,
            "data": {
                "is_heading": 1,
                "text": "Role \u2013 Administrative - Booking clerk"
            }
        },
